<!--CUT DEF section 1 --><table class="title"><tbody><tr><td><h1 class="titlemain">Download SSAX-SXML Package</h1></td></tr>
</tbody></table><p>On this page:
</p><ol class="enumerate" type="1"><li class="li-enumerate">
<a href="#hevea:bigloo">SSAX-SXML package for Bigloo</a>
</li><li class="li-enumerate"><a href="#hevea:chicken">SSAX-SXML package for Chicken</a>
</li><li class="li-enumerate"><a href="#hevea:gambit">SSAX-SXML package for Gambit</a>
</li><li class="li-enumerate"><a href="#hevea:plt">SSAX-SXML package for PLT</a>
</li><li class="li-enumerate"><a href="#hva:sisc">SSAX-SXML package for SISC</a> (ported by 
<a href="http://jottbee.org/english/index.html">Johannes Brügmann</a>)
</li></ol><p><a name="hevea:bigloo"></a>
</p><!--TOC section SSAX-SXML package for Bigloo-->
<h2 class="section"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc1">1</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;SSAX-SXML package for Bigloo</h2><!--SEC END --><p><a href="http://modis.ispras.ru/Lizorkin/Download/ssax-sxml-bigloo-060529.tgz"><em>Download the package</em></a> (last updated: 29.05.2006)</p><p>Depending on your operating system, different actions are required for
compiling/using the package:</p><!--TOC subsection Compiling/using the package under Linux-->
<h3 class="subsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc2">1.1</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Compiling/using the package under Linux</h3><!--SEC END --><!--TOC subsubsection Installing the library-->
<h4 class="subsubsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc3">1.1.1</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Installing the library</h4><!--SEC END --><p>To install the SSAX-SXML library, take the following steps:
</p><ol class="enumerate" type="1"><li class="li-enumerate">
Execute the following commands in your terminal:<br>
 <tt>$ tar zxf ssax-sxml-bigloo-060529.tgz</tt><br>
 <tt>$ cd ssax-sxml</tt><br>
 <tt>$ make lib</tt></li><li class="li-enumerate">Ensure that the value bound to the <code>DEST</code> variable in the first
non-commented line of the “<code>./Makefile</code>” is a path presented in your
“<code>/etc/ld.so.conf</code>” file.</li><li class="li-enumerate">Execute:<br>
 <tt>$ make install</tt><br>
 <tt>$ ldconfig</tt>
</li></ol><!--TOC subsubsection Running the example-->
<h4 class="subsubsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc4">1.1.2</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Running the example</h4><!--SEC END --><p>The SSAX-SXML package comes with an example that illustrates the primary
high-level functions provided in the package.</p><p>To run the example, execute:<br>
<tt>$ make</tt><br>
<tt>$ ./example.out</tt></p><!--TOC subsubsection Running tests-->
<h4 class="subsubsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc5">1.1.3</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Running tests</h4><!--SEC END --><p>The SSAX-SXML package comes with a test fixture that allows you ensure that
the package works properly on your machine.</p><p>To run tests, execute:<br>
<tt>$ ./test-sxml.out</tt></p><p>The executable “<code>test-sxml.out</code>” may take several minutes to perform all
the tests.
The executable should normally display “<code>All tests passed successfully</code>”
at the end.</p><!--TOC subsection Compiling/using the package under Windows-->
<h3 class="subsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc6">1.2</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Compiling/using the package under Windows</h3><!--SEC END --><!--TOC subsubsection Installing the library-->
<h4 class="subsubsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc7">1.2.1</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Installing the library</h4><!--SEC END --><p>To install the SSAX-SXML library, take the following steps:
</p><ol class="enumerate" type="1"><li class="li-enumerate">
Execute the following commands in your command-line:<br>
 <tt>$ tar zxf ssax-sxml-bigloo-060529.tgz</tt><br>
 <tt>$ cd ssax-sxml</tt><br>
 <tt>$ mv Makefile Makefile.linux</tt><br>
 <tt>$ mv Makefile.win Makefile</tt></li><li class="li-enumerate">Execute:<br>
 <tt>$ make dll</tt></li></ol><!--TOC subsubsection Running the example-->
<h4 class="subsubsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc8">1.2.2</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Running the example</h4><!--SEC END --><p>The SSAX-SXML package comes with an example that illustrates the primary
high-level functions provided in the package.</p><p>To run the example, execute:<br>
<tt>$ make</tt><br>
<tt>$ ./example.exe</tt></p><!--TOC subsubsection Running tests-->
<h4 class="subsubsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc9">1.2.3</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Running tests</h4><!--SEC END --><p>The SSAX-SXML package comes with a test fixture that allows you ensure that
the package works properly on your machine.</p><p>To run tests, execute:<br>
<tt>$ ./test-sxml.exe</tt></p><p>The executable should normally display “<code>All tests passed successfully</code>”
at the end.</p><div class="theorem"><b>Note&nbsp;1</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>
The Makefile in the package is specific for the recent Bigloo version&nbsp;2.7a.<br>
 For Bigloo&nbsp;2.6f, you can </em><a href="http://modis.ispras.ru/Lizorkin/Download/ssax-sxml-bigloo-060126.tgz">download the older package</a><em> (last updated: 26.01.2006).
The package for Bigloo&nbsp;2.6f will not probably be updated further.
</em></div><p><a name="hevea:chicken"></a>
</p><!--TOC section SSAX-SXML package for Chicken-->
<h2 class="section"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc10">2</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;SSAX-SXML package for Chicken</h2><!--SEC END --><p><a href="http://modis.ispras.ru/Lizorkin/Download/ssax-sxml-chicken-060529.tgz"><em>Download the package</em></a> (last updated: 29.05.2006)</p><!--TOC subsection Compiling the package-->
<h3 class="subsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc11">2.1</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Compiling the package</h3><!--SEC END --><p>To compile the SSAX-SXML package, execute the following commands in your
terminal:<br>
<tt>$ tar zxf ssax-sxml-chicken-060529.tgz</tt><br>
<tt>$ cd ssax-sxml</tt><br>
<tt>$ make</tt></p><!--TOC subsection Running the example-->
<h3 class="subsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc12">2.2</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Running the example</h3><!--SEC END --><p>The SSAX-SXML package comes with an example that illustrates the primary
high-level functions provided in the package.</p><p>To run the example, execute:<br>
<tt>$ ./example.out</tt></p><!--TOC subsection Running tests-->
<h3 class="subsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc13">2.3</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Running tests</h3><!--SEC END --><p>The SSAX-SXML package comes with a test fixture that allows you ensure that
the package works properly on your machine.</p><p>To run tests, execute:<br>
<tt>$ make test-sxml.out</tt><br>
<tt>$ ./test-sxml.out</tt></p><p><a name="hevea:gambit"></a>
</p><!--TOC section SSAX-SXML package for Gambit-->
<h2 class="section"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc14">3</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;SSAX-SXML package for Gambit</h2><!--SEC END --><p><a href="http://modis.ispras.ru/Lizorkin/Download/ssax-sxml-gambit-060529.tgz"><em>Download the package</em></a> (last updated: 29.05.2006)</p><!--TOC subsection Compiling the package-->
<h3 class="subsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc15">3.1</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Compiling the package</h3><!--SEC END --><p>To compile the SSAX-SXML package, execute the following commands in your
terminal:<br>
<tt>$ tar zxf ssax-sxml-gambit-060529.tgz</tt><br>
<tt>$ cd ssax-sxml</tt><br>
<tt>$ make</tt></p><!--TOC subsection Running the example-->
<h3 class="subsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc16">3.2</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Running the example</h3><!--SEC END --><p>The SSAX-SXML package comes with an example that illustrates the primary
high-level functions provided in the package.</p><p>To run the example, execute:<br>
<tt>$ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=.:/usr/local/lib ./example.out</tt></p><!--TOC subsection Running tests-->
<h3 class="subsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc17">3.3</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Running tests</h3><!--SEC END --><p>The SSAX-SXML package comes with a test fixture that allows you ensure that
the package works properly on your machine.</p><p>To run tests, execute:<br>
<tt>$ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=.:/usr/local/lib ./test-sxml.out</tt></p><p>The executable should normally display “<code>All tests passed successfully</code>”
at the end.</p><p><a name="hevea:plt"></a>
<a name="hva:plt"></a>
</p><!--TOC section SSAX-SXML package for PLT-->
<h2 class="section"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc18">4</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;SSAX-SXML package for PLT</h2><!--SEC END --><p><a href="http://modis.ispras.ru/Lizorkin/Download/ssax-sxml-060530.plt"><em>Download the package</em></a> (last updated: 30.05.2006)</p><!--TOC subsection Setting up the package-->
<h3 class="subsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc19">4.1</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Setting up the package</h3><!--SEC END --><ol class="enumerate" type="1"><li class="li-enumerate">
Put the downloaded file “<tt>ssax-sxml-060530.plt</tt>”
to the PLT “<tt>collect/</tt>” folder:
<ul class="itemize"><li class="li-itemize">
on Linux, this is probably “<code>/usr/local/plt/collects/</code>”
</li><li class="li-itemize">on Windows, this is probably “<code>C:\Program Files\plt\collects\</code>”
</li></ul></li><li class="li-enumerate">Execute:
<ul class="itemize"><li class="li-itemize">
on Linux:<br>
 <tt>$ setup-plt --force ssax-sxml-060530.plt</tt>
</li><li class="li-itemize">on Windows:<br>
 <tt>$ "Setup PLT.exe" --force ssax-sxml-060530.plt</tt>
</li></ul>
</li></ol><p>You can now use the SSAX-SXML library by adding the following line to your
Scheme programme:<br>
<tt>(require (lib "ssax-sxml.ss" "ssax-sxml"))</tt></p><!--TOC subsection Running the example-->
<h3 class="subsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc20">4.2</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Running the example</h3><!--SEC END --><p>The SSAX-SXML package comes with an example that illustrates the primary
high-level functions provided in the package.</p><p>You can run the example by requiring the file “<code>example.ss</code>” from
“<code>ssax-sxml</code>” library.
In particular, you can run the example from your command-line, by executing 
the following command:<br>
<tt>$ mzscheme -g</tt><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<tt>&gt; (require (lib "ssax-sxml.ss" "ssax-sxml"))</tt><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<tt>&gt; (require (lib "example.ss" "ssax-sxml"))</tt></p><!--TOC subsection Running tests-->
<h3 class="subsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc21">4.3</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Running tests</h3><!--SEC END --><p>The SSAX-SXML package comes with a test fixture that allows you ensure that
the package works properly on your machine.</p><p>To run the tests, execute:<br>
<tt>$ mzscheme -g</tt><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<tt>&gt; (require (lib "test-sxml.ss" "ssax-sxml"))</tt></p><p>The executable should normally display “<code>All tests passed successfully</code>”
at the end.</p><div class="theorem"><b>Note&nbsp;2</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>
For proper XML processing, the SSAX-SXML package requires case-sensitivity
to be turned on.
Ensure to turn case-sensitivity on when running the tests.
</em></div><div class="theorem"><b>Note&nbsp;3</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>
For PLT v.&nbsp;207 or higher, you can alternatively download the SSAX-SXML package
from the PlaneT repository:
</em><ul class="itemize"><li class="li-itemize"><em>
</em><em>for PLT (207 &lt;= version &lt; 299), add the following line to your Scheme
programme:
</em><pre class="verbatim"><em>(require (planet "sxml.ss" ("lizorkin" "sxml.plt" 2 2)))</em></pre></li><li class="li-itemize"><em>for PLT v. 299 or higher, add the following line to your programme:
</em><pre class="verbatim"><em>(require (planet "sxml.ss" ("lizorkin" "sxml.plt" 1 4)))</em></pre></li></ul><em>
</em></div><p><a name="hva:sisc"></a>
</p><!--TOC section SSAX-SXML package for SISC<BR>
 (ported and maintained by 
Johannes Brügmann)
-->
<h2 class="section"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc22">5</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;SSAX-SXML package for SISC<br>
 (ported and maintained by 
<a href="http://jottbee.org/english/index.html">Johannes Brügmann</a>)
</h2><!--SEC END --><p><a href="http://www.jottbee.org/download/ssax-sxml.jar"><em>Download the package</em></a> (last updated: 14.11.2008)</p><!--TOC subsection Setting up the package-->
<h3 class="subsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc23">5.1</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Setting up the package</h3><!--SEC END --><ol class="enumerate" type="1"><li class="li-enumerate">
Store the downloaded file “<tt>ssax-sxml.jar</tt>” somewhere on your
classpath, let’s say “<code>C:\users\MeMyselfAndI\sisc</code>”.</li><li class="li-enumerate">Tell java about your new jar-file and define the abbreviated path
<tt>sisc.ssax-sxml</tt> for it.
There are several alternative ways of doing this:
<ul class="itemize"><li class="li-itemize">
By adding the new location of the jar-file, that is, 
“<code>C:\users\MeMyselfAndI\sisc\ssax-sxml.jar</code>”, to the
<tt>CLASSPATH</tt> environment-variable</li><li class="li-itemize">By editing the “<tt>sisc.bat</tt>” or “<tt>sisc</tt>” file
directly (which is necessary anyway):
<pre class="verbatim">%JAVA% %JAVAOPT% \
       -classpath "...;C:\users\MeMyselfAndI\sisc\ssax-sxml.jar;%CLASSPATH%" \
       -Dsisc.ssax-sxml="C:\users\MeMyselfAndI\sisc" \
       -Xmx512m \
       sisc.REPL</pre></li><li class="li-itemize">For FreeBSD and tcsh users, by creating a new “sisc”-shellscript:
<ol class="enumerate" type="a"><li class="li-enumerate">
Edit the file “<tt>/home/MeMyselfAndI/.cshrc</tt>”
like <a href="http://modis.ispras.ru/Lizorkin/Download/cshrc.txt">this</a></li><li class="li-enumerate">Create the shell script “<tt>/home/MeMyselfAndI/bin/sisc</tt>”:
<pre class="verbatim">#!/usr/bin/env tcsh
source ~/.cshrc
exec $JAVA $JAVAOPT \
           -classpath "$CLASSPATH" \
     sisc.REPL -h /usr/local/share/sisc/sisc.shp \
               $argv</pre></li></ol>
</li></ul><p>Make sure that the abbreviated path is <tt>sisc.ssax-sxml</tt>, or otherwise
edit “<tt>ssax-sxml.scm</tt>” and the dependent files.
Exception: <code>(require-library 'sisc/foo/ssax-sxml-code)</code> should work
anyway.
</p></li></ol><!--TOC subsection Using the libraries-->
<h3 class="subsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc24">5.2</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Using the libraries</h3><!--SEC END --><p>Now start sisc and load the libraries you need.
This port comes with SSAX-SXML,
<a href="http://celtic.benderweb.net/sxml-match/index.html">SXML-Match</a>, and
<a href="http://celtic.benderweb.net/webit/docs/xquery-pre/">XQuery</a> support:
</p><pre class="verbatim">SISC (1.16.6)
&gt; (require-library 'sisc/ssax-sxml/ssax-sxml-code)
(sisc/ssax-sxml/ssax-sxml-code
  (sisc/libs/srfi 
    ...
    )
&gt; (require-library 'sisc/ssax-sxml/sxml-match)
(sisc/ssax-sxml/sxml-match)
&gt; (require-library 'sisc/ssax-sxml/query)
(sisc/ssax-sxml/query)</pre><!--TOC subsection Running tests-->
<h3 class="subsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc25">5.3</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Running tests</h3><!--SEC END --><p>You can run all the tests that are shipped with SSAX-SXML to verify
that everything works in one of the following ways:
</p><ul class="itemize"><li class="li-itemize">
Evaluate:<br>
 <tt>&gt; (require-library ’sisc/ssax-sxml/doc/tests/all-tests)</tt><br>
 or</li><li class="li-itemize">Unpack the JAR-file using unzip (maybe rename that file to <tt>.zip</tt>)
in a place of your choice and change to subdirectory
<tt>sisc/ssax-sxml/doc/tests</tt> and then evaluate:<br>
 <tt>&gt; (load "all-tests.scm")</tt>
</li></ul><!--TOC subsection Additional notes-->
<h3 class="subsection"><!--SEC ANCHOR --><a name="htoc26">5.4</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;Additional notes</h3><!--SEC END --><ol class="enumerate" type="1"><li class="li-enumerate">
Have a look at “<tt>sisc/ssax-sxml/doc/tests/vsxml-tutorial.scm</tt>”
in the package, the file contains an xtest-assertion for every example from
<a href="http://modis.ispras.ru/Lizorkin/sxml-tutorial.html">SXML-Tutorial</a>
and a list of modules to import.</li><li class="li-enumerate">Differences to other SSAX-SXML-Ports:
<ul class="itemize"><li class="li-itemize">
module <tt>sxpath</tt> is called <tt>mdl:sxpath</tt>
(if you know how to fix that, please let me know)
</li><li class="li-itemize">module <tt>txpath</tt> is called <tt>mdl:txpath</tt>
(if you know how to fix that, please let me know)
</li><li class="li-itemize">case-sensitivity is achieved in SISC with <code>'|FooBar|</code>, so some
examples of the SXML-Tutorial need to be adopted for this
</li><li class="li-itemize">the lib contains two versions of the code: 
<ul class="itemize"><li class="li-itemize">
<tt>sisc/ssax-sxml/ssax-sxml</tt> is modularized and scheme source code
</li><li class="li-itemize"><tt>sisc/ssax-sxml/ssax-sxml-code</tt> is a “all-in-one” single file
with compiled code for little better performance and faster loading
(loads in max 4 seconds on Turion64 X2)
</li></ul>
</li></ul></li><li class="li-enumerate">Bug-reports: please send bugreports that are limited to the
SISC-port to <a href="mailto:bugs@jottbee.org">bugs@jottbee.org</a>
</li></ol><p><br>

<a href="http://modis.ispras.ru/Lizorkin/xml-functional.html"><em>Back to XML-Functional page</em></a></p><!--CUT END -->
